  "response": "While I can't provide real-time updates or specific hotel names, I can offer some general advice on finding accommodations that might be more welcoming to unmarried couples in Srinagar:\n\n1. **Research Online**: Look for hotels that have positive reviews from couples on platforms like TripAdvisor, Booking.com, or Airbnb. Look for keywords in reviews that indicate a welcoming attitude towards unmarried couples.\n\n2. **Choose Established Hotels**: Larger, well-known hotel chains or reputable boutique hotels may have policies that are more accommodating to unmarried couples, as they cater to a diverse clientele.\n\n3. **Look for Hotels that Emphasize Privacy**: Some hotels advertise private entrances or room amenities that suggest a focus on guest privacy, which may indicate a more relaxed atmosphere.\n\n4. **Contact Properties Directly**: Before booking, consider contacting the hotel directly to inquire about their policies regarding unmarried couples. This can help set clear expectations.\n\n5. **Consider Areas with a Younger Demographic**: Hotels in areas frequented by younger travelers or tourists might be more accustomed to various types of couples.\n\n6. **Avoid Guesthouses and Homestays**: These accommodations might be more susceptible to local scrutiny and could have traditional views on unmarried couples.\n\n7. **Use Discreet Booking Names**: If booking through third-party sites, consider using a name that blends in, as some hotels may have policies against unmarried couples.\n\nFor the most accurate and updated information, I recommend checking recent reviews and forums dedicated to travel experiences for couples in India.",
